    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-05-13T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-05-13T21:00:00-05:00" n="86"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d86">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">110.11/5–1451: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hong Kong</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McConaughy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret   priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hong Kong</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-05-14T11:00:00+09:00"
                            >May 14, 1951—11 a. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3369. To Acheson for Dep Under Secy Matthews,<note n="1" xml:id="d86fn1">The
                        telegram was circulated to Frederick E. Nolting, Special Assistant to the
                        Deputy Under Secretary; Nitze; and Merchant.</note> Marshall and Chase have
                    made available of all known possible contacts. They plan wait till May 19.
                    Thereupon if nothing to justify their continuation here has appeared they will
                    return to Washington. Meantime they request any further instructions or relevant
                    info from you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">McConaughy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
